      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span at least two load levels or two fixation torque settings to characterise condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard load configuration (6° angulation, 35 mm offset) and single fixation torque (4 Nm). A second torque level was planned but not executed due to specimen availability constraints. This factor is below required level and represents a known gap; the deficiency is accepted given that the standard configuration is the regulatory reference condition and model predictions are conservative at higher torques based on the UQ campaign narrative."
