    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for a Medium assurance, model risk level 3 assessment. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 standard configuration is the sole regulatory reference condition and that the UQ campaign — described in the validation report narrative — demonstrates robustness of model predictions across the plausible range of fixation torque values. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative error < 10%) across both laboratories. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
